Wildcard Justifications
-----------------------
The following statements use wildcard patterns. Each is documented here
for security audit purposes.

ec2-instance-profile.json
  S3ModelArtifactsRead / S3ModelArtifactsWrite
    <BUCKET_NAME>/* scoped to a single bucket. Object paths vary by
    training run and model output.

  BedrockImportJob
    model-import-job/* required because job IDs are generated at
    runtime. Scoped to account and region.

  BedrockCustomModel
    custom-model/* required because the model name is unknown at setup
    time. For production: replace with the specific model ARN after
    import (e.g. custom-model/abc123def456).

  CloudWatchLogging
    Log group wildcard (:*) is required by CloudWatch Logs to cover
    the log group and its streams.

bedrock-import-role.json
  S3ReadModelArtifacts
    <BUCKET_NAME>/* scoped to a single bucket. The Bedrock service
    reads model artifacts at various paths during import.
